SIMPLE: grateful
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Grateful
<hw>Grate"ful</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Grate</ets>,
a. + <ets>full</ets>; cf. F. <ets>gr⟦eacute⟧</ets> thanks, good will,
fr. L. <ets>gratum</ets>, neut. of <ets>gratus</ets> agreeable,
grateful. See <er>Grate</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Having a due sense of benefits received; kindly disposed toward one
from whom a favor has been received; willing to acknowledge and repay,
or give thanks for, benefits; <as>as, a <ex>grateful</ex>
heart</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A <qex>grateful</qex> mind⟦br⟧
By owing, owes not, but still pays.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Affording pleasure; pleasing to the senses;
gratifying; delicious; <as>as, a <ex>grateful</ex> present; food
<ex>grateful</ex> to the palate; <ex>grateful</ex> sleep</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Now golden fruits on loaded branches shine,⟦br⟧
And <qex>grateful</qex> clusters swell.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Thankful; pleasing; acceptable; gratifying;
agreeable; welcome; delightful; delicious.</syn></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Grate"ful*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Grate"ful*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Grater</ent>⟦br⟧
